# #Misfits Change /Add/
# Thermal ambience messages — sent privately to the player only.
# Appear in the local chat box with no name attached (like a /do or subtle admin prayer).
# These convey the felt heat and cold of Wendover, Utah's desert salt flats — no damage, pure RP flavor.

# --- VERY HOT (salt flats midday, ≥ 313 K / ~40°C / 104°F) ---
thermal-ambience-very-hot-1 = The salt flats radiate heat in waves. Sweat runs freely down the back of your neck.
thermal-ambience-very-hot-2 = The air feels thick and oven-hot against every inch of exposed skin.
thermal-ambience-very-hot-3 = Your shirt clings to your back. The ground shimmers in the distance.
thermal-ambience-very-hot-4 = You can feel the heat pressing down from above and bouncing off the white surface below. There is nowhere to hide from it.
thermal-ambience-very-hot-5 = The salt crust reflects the sun hard enough to sting your eyes. Your temples throb.

# --- HOT (warm afternoon, 308–313 K / ~35–40°C / 95–104°F) ---
thermal-ambience-hot-1 = The afternoon air is heavy with dry desert heat.
thermal-ambience-hot-2 = A thin sheen of perspiration builds under your collar.
thermal-ambience-hot-3 = The sun burns steadily overhead. Your mouth is dry.
thermal-ambience-hot-4 = The heat is persistent and oppressive, the kind that makes you consider whether you are being dramatic or just appropriately cautious.

# --- WARM (comfortable-but-notable, 303–308 K / ~30–35°C / 86–95°F) ---
thermal-ambience-warm-1 = The day is warm — pleasantly so, if you are not doing anything strenuous.
thermal-ambience-warm-2 = A light sweat prickles under your arms. Not unpleasant, just present.
thermal-ambience-warm-3 = The sun sits high and the ground holds its heat, but you can manage.

# --- COOL (evening chill, 278–288 K / ~5–15°C / 41–59°F) ---
thermal-ambience-cool-1 = The temperature has dropped noticeably since sundown. Your skin prickles in the cooler air.
thermal-ambience-cool-2 = A restless chill stirs through the dusty air as night settles.
thermal-ambience-cool-3 = The flat radiates the last of its stored warmth upward into the dark. Enough to notice the cold coming.
thermal-ambience-cool-4 = You pull your collar tighter. The desert nights have no mercy for those who expected the day to last.

# --- COLD (deep night, 273–278 K / ~0–5°C / 32–41°F) ---
thermal-ambience-cold-1 = Your breath fogs in the cold air. You fight the urge to shiver.
thermal-ambience-cold-2 = The cold has settled in properly now — a steady, bone-deep chill with no wind to blame it on.
thermal-ambience-cold-3 = Goosebumps rise and hold. Your fingertips are starting to feel the cold first, as always.
thermal-ambience-cold-4 = The salt flats are merciless at night. The same open emptiness that bakes you at noon freezes you now.

# --- VERY COLD (frigid pre-dawn, < 273 K / below 0°C / 32°F) ---
thermal-ambience-very-cold-1 = The cold bites into your face and hands. Subzero out here, and the ground offers no warmth.
thermal-ambience-very-cold-2 = Your breath comes out in hard white clouds. You cannot stop shivering.
thermal-ambience-very-cold-3 = Every inhale stings the back of your throat. Movement is the only option you have left.
thermal-ambience-very-cold-4 = The desert has flipped every comfort it offered at noon into something hostile and unforgiving.

# --- SWEATING (body thermoregulation — internal heat, ≥ 310 K body temp) ---
thermal-ambience-sweating-1 = Sweat runs down your spine in a slow, steady line.
thermal-ambience-sweating-2 = Your face flushes. Your body is working hard to shed the heat.
thermal-ambience-sweating-3 = Perspiration soaks into the back of your collar. Your skin feels slick and hot.

# --- SHIVERING (body thermoregulation — internal cold, ≤ 286 K body temp) ---
thermal-ambience-shivering-1 = A shiver runs through you before you can suppress it.
thermal-ambience-shivering-2 = Your muscles tremble in short, involuntary bursts. The cold is getting in.
thermal-ambience-shivering-3 = Your teeth want to chatter. You press your jaw shut and breathe through it.
